        <num>CC 1886</num>
        <heading>1886.  Delegation of performance</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1886.  Delegation of performance
A delegation of performance by an obligor to a third person is effective when that person binds himself to perform.
A delegation effects a novation only when the obligee expressly discharges the original obligor.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=109130</p>
